NATIONWIDE polling ahead of this week’s referendum suggests that the nation is split in two between Yes and No; many families across Scotland are no different Video report: Picking up the pieces after the vote NATIONWIDE polling ahead of this week’s referendum suggests that the nation is split in two between Yes and No; many families across Scotland are no different.

Ray Philp spoke to the Primrose family from Paisley to discuss their difference of opinion, and the artist whose installation provides a useful visual metaphor for the reconciliation ahead after the euphoria of the result.

 